<item>
            <title>[SPARK-22145] Issues with driver re-starting on mesos (supervise)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-22145</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are two issues with driver re-starting on mesos using the supervise flag:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We need to add spark.mesos.driver.frameworkId to the reloaded properties for checkpointing, otherwise the new frameworkId propagated by the dispatcher will be overwritten by the checkpointed data.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Unique driver task ids are not used by the dispatcher:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MESOS-4737&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MESOS-4737&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MESOS-3070&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MESOS-3070&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
This issue is the same in principle as in the case with standalone mode where the master needs to re-launch drivers with a new appId (driverId) to deal with net partitions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

</description>
